definition: to park (a car etc)/to moor (a boat etc)/to leave sth (in a place)
to put/to place/to release/to free/to let go/to let out/to set off (fireworks)

sentences.english: You don't know how to park a bicycle straight.
sentences.chinese: 你甚至不知道怎樣停放自行車。

sentences.english: It has three car-parks, which can hold more than 100 cars.
sentences.chinese: 擁有停車場三個，可停放100輛汽車。

sentences.english: The parked car is obstructing the traffic.
sentences.chinese: 所停放的汽車妨礙了交通。

sentences.english: In front of the teaching building are many students' bikes.
sentences.chinese: 在教學樓前停放着許多學生的自行車。

sentences.english: There are lots of b, Ikes parked. Illegally around here.
sentences.chinese: 這裏有許多自行車違規停放。

sentences.english: Make sure that the vehicle is standing on a level surface.
sentences.chinese: 請確保車輛停放於水平表面。
要把車輛停放在明亮的區域。

sentences.english: Does the facility maintain a parking area for private vehicles separate from the shipping . loading dock and cargo areas ?
sentences.chinese: 工廠是否設有私家車停放區並與出貨車停放區分開？

sentences.english: Does the facility maintain a parking area for private vehicles separate from the shipping . loading dock and cargo areas ?
sentences.chinese: 工廠是否設有私家車停放區並與出貨車停放區分開？

sentences.english: The garage is big, too. It has to be to accommodate the Prince’s hundreds of cars.
sentences.chinese: 車庫也很大，用來停放王子的數百輛汽車。

sentences.english: Right before you enter the airplane, fold up and leave the carriage at the end of the ramp.
sentences.chinese: 在你登機之前，把車摺疊好停放在斜坡的底下。

sentences.english: An passenger car "Equality" stopped at Sugar Line Tou-liou Station, 1968.
sentences.chinese: 停放於臺糖公司斗六車站的平等號客車。

sentences.english: Improperly parked cars will be issued a violation.
sentences.chinese: 未依規定停放者，以違規停車論。

sentences.english: A traffic warden sees that all cars are properly parked.
sentences.chinese: 交通督察官檢查所有車輛是否遵守規則停放。

sentences.english: The car should be on a level surface with the parking brake on and engine off.
sentences.chinese: 將汽車停放在水平的地面上，關閉發動機並拉緊手剎。

definition: to pull up (stop one's vehicle)/to park/(of a machine) to stop working/to stall
to travel along a route (of vehicles etc)
parking spot/unloading point/garage place/stand for taxi
(of a car, ship, train etc) to enter
